 056:     """
 057:     A class for internal representation of atom types. Using unique objects
 058:     rather than strings allows us to use fast pointer comparisons instead of
 059:     slow string comparisons, as well as store extra metadata. In particular,
 060:     we store metadata describing the atom type's hierarchy with regard to other
 061:     atom types, and the atom types that can result when various actions
 062:     involving this atom type are taken. The attributes are:
 063: 
 064:     =================== =================== ====================================
 065:     Attribute           Type                Description
 066:     =================== =================== ====================================
 067:     `label`             ``str``             A unique label for the atom type
 068:     `generic`           ``list``            The atom types that are more generic than this one
 069:     `specific`          ``list``            The atom types that are more specific than this one
 070:     `incrementBond`     ``list``            The atom type(s) that result when an adjacent bond's order is incremented
 071:     `decrementBond`     ``list``            The atom type(s) that result when an adjacent bond's order is decremented
 072:     `formBond`          ``list``            The atom type(s) that result when a new single bond is formed to this atom type
 073:     `breakBond`         ``list``            The atom type(s) that result when an existing single bond to this atom type is broken
 074:     `incrementRadical`  ``list``            The atom type(s) that result when the number of radical electrons is incremented
 075:     `decrementRadical`  ``list``            The atom type(s) that result when the number of radical electrons is decremented
 076:     `incrementLonePair` ``list``            The atom type(s) that result when the number of lone electron pairs is incremented
 077:     `decrementLonePair` ``list``            The atom type(s) that result when the number of lone electron pairs is decremented
 078: 
 079:     The following features are what are required in a given atomtype. Any int in the list is acceptable.
 080:     An empty list is a wildcard
 081:     'single'            ''list''            The total number of single bonds on the atom
 082:     'allDouble'         ''list''            The total number of double bonds on the atom
 083:     'rDouble'           ''list''            The number of double bonds to any non-oxygen, nonsulfur
 084:     'oDouble'           ''list''            The number of double bonds to oxygen
 085:     'sDouble'           ''list''            The number of double bonds to sulfur
 086:     'triple'            ''list''            The total number of triple bonds on the atom
 087:     'benzene'           ''list''            The total number of benzene bonds on the atom
 088:     'lonePairs'         ''list''            The number of lone pairs on the atom
 089:     =================== =================== ====================================
 090: 
 091:     """
 092:
